<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="190" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,605,150,213]" box="[151,303,186,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,295,186,213]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 4" captionStart-1="FIGURE 5" captionStartId-0="8.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionStartId-1="9.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox-0="[152,1436,307,1933]" captionTargetBox-1="[157,1424,184,1698]" captionTargetId-0="figure-100@8.[151,1436,306,1938]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@9.[151,1437,181,1704]" captionTargetPageId-0="8" captionTargetPageId-1="9" captionText-0="FIGURE 4A–E. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female.A—body, lateral view; B—the same, dorsal view; C— head and anterior part of pronotum, dorsal view; D—head and anterior part of pronotum, lateral view; E—head, frontal view." captionText-1="FIGURE 5A–H. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female: A—left fore femur, lateral view; B—left mid femur, lateral view; C—left hind femur, lateral view; D—left hind tibia, lateral view; E—left posterior tarsus, lateral view; F—subgenital plate of female, ventral view; male, paratype: G—body in dorsal view; H—body in lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Figures 4–5</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,2013]" box="[151,1274,258,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,397,258,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[304,397,258,285]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Female.</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Body moderate, slender, body surface smooth and interspersed with granules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,268,294,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,261,294,321]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head and eyes distinctly exserted above pronotal surface (
<figureCitation box="[928,1010,294,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,307,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[151,1436,306,1938]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4A–E. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female.A—body, lateral view; B—the same, dorsal view; C— head and anterior part of pronotum, dorsal view; D—head and anterior part of pronotum, lateral view; E—head, frontal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Vertex narrow, in dorsal view, width of vertex between eyes 0.6 times width of compound eye (
<figureCitation box="[802,884,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,307,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[151,1436,306,1938]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4A–E. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female.A—body, lateral view; B—the same, dorsal view; C— head and anterior part of pronotum, dorsal view; D—head and anterior part of pronotum, lateral view; E—head, frontal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
); a little narrower in front; anterior margin of fastigium narrowly rounded and not surpassing anterior margin of eye; median carina visible anteriorly; lateral margins turned backward and reaching upper margin of eye; vertex uneven with paired fossulae. In lateral view, frontal costa slightly visible between eyes (
<figureCitation box="[484,567,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,307,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[151,1436,306,1938]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4A–E. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female.A—body, lateral view; B—the same, dorsal view; C— head and anterior part of pronotum, dorsal view; D—head and anterior part of pronotum, lateral view; E—head, frontal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
), protruded anteriorly and broadly rounded between antennal grooves. In frontal view, vertex with V-shaped concavity, bottom of which reaching one-fourth of upper inner margins of eyes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,307,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[151,1436,306,1938]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4A–E. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female.A—body, lateral view; B—the same, dorsal view; C— head and anterior part of pronotum, dorsal view; D—head and anterior part of pronotum, lateral view; E—head, frontal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig 4e</figureCitation>
); lateral margins barely reaching the level of upper margin of eyes; frontal costa bifurcated above lateral ocelli, longitudinal furrow divergent between antennae, width of longitudinal furrow of frontal ridge very narrower than antennal groove diameter (
<figureCitation box="[450,532,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,307,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[151,1436,306,1938]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4A–E. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female.A—body, lateral view; B—the same, dorsal view; C— head and anterior part of pronotum, dorsal view; D—head and anterior part of pronotum, lateral view; E—head, frontal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
). Antennae short, filiform, antennal grooves inserted between inferior margins of compound eyes (
<figureCitation box="[341,424,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,307,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[151,1436,306,1938]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4A–E. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female.A—body, lateral view; B—the same, dorsal view; C— head and anterior part of pronotum, dorsal view; D—head and anterior part of pronotum, lateral view; E—head, frontal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
), 15-segmented, the 10th and 11th segment are the longest, about 7–8 times longer than its width. Eyes globose, lateral (paired) ocelli located in slightly below the middle of compound eye height.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,291,690,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotal surface smooth and interspersed with dense granules (
<figureCitation box="[995,1078,690,716]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,307,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[151,1436,306,1938]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4A–E. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female.A—body, lateral view; B—the same, dorsal view; C— head and anterior part of pronotum, dorsal view; D—head and anterior part of pronotum, lateral view; E—head, frontal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
). In dorsal view, anterior margin of pronotum truncate; lateral carinae of prozona parallel; median carina entire; obtuse humeral angles; with a pair of inconspicuous interhumeral carinae; hind pronotal process narrow and long cone-shaped, reaching or approaching apex of hind tibia. In profile, median carina of pronotum slightly undulate before shoulders and straight behind shoulders. Lateral lobes of pronotum turning outwardly, posterior angles directed distinctly transversely, truncate, apex of posterior angles bearing triangular. Posterior margins of lateral lobes of pronotum with ventral sinus and tegminal (upper) sinus. Tegmina long, ovate, apex rounded. Hind wings reaching or slightly surpassing apex of hind pronotal process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,261,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Legs.</emphasis>
Fore and middle femora with carinated, margins finely serrated, dorsal and ventral margins of fore femora straight (
<figureCitation box="[250,331,1014,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1437,181,1704]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–H. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female: A—left fore femur, lateral view; B—left mid femur, lateral view; C—left hind femur, lateral view; D—left hind tibia, lateral view; E—left posterior tarsus, lateral view; F—subgenital plate of female, ventral view; male, paratype: G—body in dorsal view; H—body in lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
), dorsal and ventral margins of middle femora slightly undulated (
<figureCitation box="[1073,1156,1014,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1437,181,1704]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–H. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female: A—left fore femur, lateral view; B—left mid femur, lateral view; C—left hind femur, lateral view; D—left hind tibia, lateral view; E—left posterior tarsus, lateral view; F—subgenital plate of female, ventral view; male, paratype: G—body in dorsal view; H—body in lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 5b</figureCitation>
); middle femur narrower than visible part of tegmen in width. Hind femora robust and short, 3.6 times as long as wide; margins finely serrated (
<figureCitation box="[223,304,1086,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1437,181,1704]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–H. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female: A—left fore femur, lateral view; B—left mid femur, lateral view; C—left hind femur, lateral view; D—left hind tibia, lateral view; E—left posterior tarsus, lateral view; F—subgenital plate of female, ventral view; male, paratype: G—body in dorsal view; H—body in lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 5c</figureCitation>
); antegenicular denticles right angled and genicular denticles acute. Outer side of hind tibia with 5–6 spines, inner side with 7–8 spines (
<figureCitation box="[542,625,1122,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1437,181,1704]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–H. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female: A—left fore femur, lateral view; B—left mid femur, lateral view; C—left hind femur, lateral view; D—left hind tibia, lateral view; E—left posterior tarsus, lateral view; F—subgenital plate of female, ventral view; male, paratype: G—body in dorsal view; H—body in lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 5d</figureCitation>
). First segment of posterior tarsi equal to third in length, three pulvilli of first segment of posterior tarsi equal in length, apices of all pulvilli obtuse (
<figureCitation box="[995,1077,1158,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1437,181,1704]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–H. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female: A—left fore femur, lateral view; B—left mid femur, lateral view; C—left hind femur, lateral view; D—left hind tibia, lateral view; E—left posterior tarsus, lateral view; F—subgenital plate of female, ventral view; male, paratype: G—body in dorsal view; H—body in lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 5e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1194,1221]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Ovipositor narrow and long, length of upper valvulae 4.5 times its width, upper and lower valvulae with slender saw-like teeth. Length of subgenital plate nearly equal to its width, middle of posterior margin of subgenital plate concave and then triangularly projecting (
<figureCitation box="[764,843,1266,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1437,181,1704]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–H. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female: A—left fore femur, lateral view; B—left mid femur, lateral view; C—left hind femur, lateral view; D—left hind tibia, lateral view; E—left posterior tarsus, lateral view; F—subgenital plate of female, ventral view; male, paratype: G—body in dorsal view; H—body in lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Fig. 5f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,1302,1329]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body dark brown. Frons dark brown. Hind wings black. Lateral lobes of pronotum and lateral of abdomen with black and white spots. Fore and middle femora brown; fore and middle brown and each with two dark transverse spots. Hind femur brown and outer side with two blackish spots. Hind tibia dark brown, with two light rings in the middle. Sternites of thorax and abdomen black, subgenital plate black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,265,1446,1473]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Male.</emphasis>
Similar to female, but smaller and narrower (
<figureCitation box="[784,897,1446,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1437,181,1704]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–H. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female: A—left fore femur, lateral view; B—left mid femur, lateral view; C—left hind femur, lateral view; D—left hind tibia, lateral view; E—left posterior tarsus, lateral view; F—subgenital plate of female, ventral view; male, paratype: G—body in dorsal view; H—body in lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[837,865,1446,1473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" unit="g" value="5.0">5g</quantity>
–h
</figureCitation>
). Width of vertex between eyes 0.5 times width of compound eye (
<figureCitation box="[366,450,1482,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1437,181,1704]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5A–H. Xistra nigriabdominis Deng, sp. nov., holotype female: A—left fore femur, lateral view; B—left mid femur, lateral view; C—left hind femur, lateral view; D—left hind tibia, lateral view; E—left posterior tarsus, lateral view; F—subgenital plate of female, ventral view; male, paratype: G—body in dorsal view; H—body in lateral view." pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[420,450,1482,1509]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" unit="g" value="5.0">5g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); middle femur nearly equal to visible part of tegmen in width. Subgenital plate short, cone-shaped, apex bifurcated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,2013]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,448,1554,1580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Measurements (mm)</emphasis>
. Length of body: 
<specimenCount box="[652,672,1554,1581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
10.0–10.5, 
<specimenCount box="[800,821,1555,1581]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
